The paper focuses on security, privacy, and trust in smart and connected M-IoT networks, which are all related to the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the evolution of wireless infrastructure and the use of sensors and machines, which are relevant to the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also covers various challenges, technologies, and open issues related to M-IoT, which are relevant to the field of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the physical layer security and handover protections in M-IoT, which are relevant to the field of distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
